Description:
This book aims to help professionals in the offshore area to better understand the meanings of some specific terms, as well as other trivial terms in technical English in Oil and Gas. Because, at the same time, there are several online translation tools and a database of Massive data at our disposal today, there is also a major barrier to access to these databases by professionals when on board during offshore work. Due to the lack of adequate access, we are often limited to resources such as English, which is almost mandatory in the offshore world these days.
Therefore, I seek to offer an “offline” resource so that many professionals do not get lost or miss opportunities because of their English translations.

WHAT ARE THE MAIN ADVANTAGES OF THIS BOOK?
Current and simplified content;
"Offline" resource for Offshore Professionals;
Ideal for English Teachers to increase their knowledge;
Ideal for Translators from Foreign Companies;
Ideal for the general public who want to know more about Offshore.

WHO IS THIS MATERIAL FOR?
Offshore professionals;
Oil and Gas Industry Professionals;
Managers;
Teachers;
Entrepreneurs;
General public with no restriction on age or graduation level.

